        Official Singles Chart on 30/10/2020

        30 October 2020 - 5 November 2020

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        Trebor

        2nd November 2020
        3
        Vote score

        So... the tracks I'm interesting in!

        'REALLY LOVE'
        Glad to see Craig back again, after a great comeback... sounding just as brilliant as 20yrs ago... Hope this does excel to #1!

        'SWEET MELODY'
        I know some will love & some will hate... But I think this is a standout track from LM in recent years... A proper fusion of styles!

        'MIDNIGHT SKY'
        Not a fan of Miley but this has really grown on me... Probably at the same rate as the general public so it seems!

        'TICK TOCK'
        Wasn't keen at first but after a week I realised this was a great track... I thought Clean Bandit had another #1 in the bag? Doesn't seem to be catching on sadly!

        'LASTING LOVER'
        It doesn't sound like a sigala track to me... But I love how James's voice atatches his voice to different genres so well! 'We got love' denied being huge in my opinion!

        'LEVITATING'
        I'm really glad this is gaining in popularity... I still love the BM remix but I think that's due to Madonna and Missy tbh... Love it!

        'HEAD & HEART'
        Still one of few songs to get my head bopping & shoulders moving right now... Looking forward to Joel's next track!

        'DIAMONDS'
        So Sam's album is out now... Great song & I hope the album boosts it's sales... A standout track from the album!

        'TRAIN WRECK'
        Is this another tictok thing? I like James but does it really deserve this kind of recognition? I'm not entirely sure!

        'LOOKING FOR ME'
        Still sounds great... Simple melody and vocals but still can't it just works as a good feel tune!

        'COME OVER'
        This hasn't had the recognition it deserves... Rudimental & Anne-Marie... Is it that it was too 2000?

        'I MISS U'
        A decent EDM track... It's catchy but it's not grabbing me like probably all of Jax's previous efforts... I'm hoping this is an interlude to some new great collaborations!

        'ONE TOO MANY'
        #40 is an insult if that is the peak of this... Took me a week but this has really grown on me & both Keith & Pink deserve more! I love listening to this!

        'I DON'T WANNA KNOW'
        I'm curious to see how this performs... I'm unsure right now! Some EDM reinventions work. Punctuals version may be a grower!

        'TOO MANY NIGHTS'
        This just hasn't caught on for some reason... Hope 220 kid eventually gets a top 40 with this... It deserves it!

        Also...
        'Breaking me' & 'Roses'... Someone please tell me why they didn't enter the dance chart?
